---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/UI/Container.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - All Leaders Initiative cares about your data"
  metaTitle="Privacy Policy - All Leaders Initiative"
  metaDescription="Information on how we process and protect your personal data in accordance with GDPR."
  lang="en"
  alternateUrls={{ fr: '/privacy', en: '/en/privacy' }}
>
  <Container>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-6">
      <h1 class="pt-[12vh] pb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2024 | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none">
        <p class="lead mb-8">
          This privacy policy describes the manner in which <span class="brand-text">
            ALL <span class="leaders">LEADERS</span>
            <span class="thin">INITIATIVE</span>
          </span> (hereinafter "the organization") collects, processes, protects and manages the personal
          data of visitors and clients to the website <strong>all-leaders.fr</strong>, in accordance
          with Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons (GDPR)
          and applicable data protection legislation.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Identity and contact details of the controller</h2>

        <p>
          The data controller as defined by the GDPR is: <br />
          <span class="brand-text">
            ALL <span class="leaders">LEADERS</span>
            <span class="thin">INITIATIVE</span>
          </span><br />
          Legal form: Sole trader / Micro-enterprise<br />
          Domicile: France
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Data controller contact:</strong><br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:contact@all-leaders.fr">contact@all-leaders.fr</a><br />
          For all requests relating to data protection.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Personal data collected</h2>

        <p>Personal data that may be collected via the website and contact forms include:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Identification data:</strong> full name, first name, title (job title)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact data:</strong> professional email address, telephone number
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Professional data:</strong> organization name, business sector, team size
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Navigation data:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, pages visited, duration
            of visits, source of traffic (via analytics services)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Communication data:</strong> content of any message, request or comment transmitted
            via contact forms
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-6">
          <em
            >No sensitive personal data (racial origin, religious beliefs, genetic data, etc.) is
            intentionally collected. The website is not intended for children under 16 years of age.</em
          >
        </p>

        <h2>3. Purposes of data processing</h2>

        <p>Your data is processed for the following legitimate purposes:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Management of contact requests:</strong> processing, follow-up and response to your
            information requests or appointment requests
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business development:</strong> maintaining contact, sending proposals tailored to
            your organization, communication about offers and events
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Service delivery:</strong> implementation and follow-up of coaching and training services
            ordered
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analysis and improvement:</strong> statistical analysis of the website, audience measurement,
            continuous improvement of the user experience
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal obligations:</strong> compliance with applicable legal and regulatory provisions
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Security:</strong> prevention of fraud and service abuse
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Legal basis for processing</h2>

        <p>Data processing is based on:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> operation, security and improvement of the website and
            services
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent:</strong> receipt of business communications or subscriptions to newsletters
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contract performance:</strong> management of quotation requests and ordered services
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal obligations:</strong> data retention for evidentiary or accounting purposes
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Recipients and data sharing</h2>

        <p>Your data is shared only with the following recipients:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong
              >The <span class="brand-text">
                ALL <span class="leaders">LEADERS</span>
                <span class="thin">INITIATIVE</span>
              </span> team:</strong
            > for processing your requests and providing services
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical service providers:</strong> website hosting provider, analytics tools (Google
            Analytics 4), email platforms
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal authorities:</strong> where legally required
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>No sale or transfer to commercial third parties</strong> is carried out. Your data is
          never exchanged for consideration.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Data transfer outside the European Union</h2>

        <p>
          Personal data is processed primarily within the European Union. Certain third-party
          services (notably Google Analytics 4) may involve transfers to the United States, on the
          basis of the Data Privacy Framework (DPF) approved by the European Commission.
        </p>

        <p>
          <span class="brand-text">
            ALL <span class="leaders">LEADERS</span>
            <span class="thin">INITIATIVE</span>
          </span> implements appropriate safeguards required by the GDPR for these transfers.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Data retention period</h2>

        <p>Data is retained for the following periods:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Contact data (prospects):</strong> 3 years from the date of last interaction (or withdrawal
            of consent)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Customer data:</strong> for the duration of the contract + 3 years (accounting obligation)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Navigation data (analytics):</strong> maximum 14 months
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Server access logs:</strong> 1 month (security)
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Cookies and tracking technologies</h2>

        <p>
          The website uses cookies and similar technologies. Please consult our <a
            href="/en/cookies">cookies policy</a
          > for complete details on the cookies installed, their purposes and how to manage your preferences.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Security measures</h2>

        <p>
          <span class="brand-text">
            ALL <span class="leaders">LEADERS</span>
            <span class="thin">INITIATIVE</span>
          </span> implements technical and organizational measures to protect the confidentiality and
          integrity of your data:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>HTTPS protocol to encrypt transmissions</li>
          <li>Secure authentication of access</li>
          <li>Limitation of data access (need-to-know basis)</li>
          <li>Regular data backups</li>
          <li>Disaster recovery plan</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-4">
          <em
            >However, no system is 100% secure. In the event of a security incident affecting your
            data, you will be notified without delay.</em
          >
        </p>

        <h2>10. Your rights regarding your personal data</h2>

        <p>
          In accordance with the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Right of access:</strong> obtain a copy of your data and details of how it is processed
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to rectification:</strong> correct inaccurate or incomplete data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to erasure (right to be forgotten):</strong> deletion of your data (under certain
            conditions)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to restrict processing:</strong> request temporary suspension of processing
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to data portability:</strong> receive your data in a structured and standard
            format
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to object:</strong> object to certain processing (business development in particular)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right not to be subject:</strong> to automated decision-making (profiling)
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-6">
          To exercise these rights, submit a written request to: <a
            href="mailto:contact@all-leaders.fr">contact@all-leaders.fr</a
          >, accompanied by a copy of proof of identity.
        </p>

        <p>
          You also have the right to withdraw your consent at any time (for processing based on
          consent).
        </p>

        <h2>11. Unsubscription and preference management</h2>

        <p>
          If you receive business communications and wish to unsubscribe, click the unsubscribe link
          present at the bottom of each email or contact us directly at: <a
            href="mailto:contact@all-leaders.fr">contact@all-leaders.fr</a
          >
        </p>

        <h2>12. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>

        <p>
          If you believe your data protection rights are not being respected, you have the right to
          lodge a complaint with the appropriate supervisory authority, in particular:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>ICO</strong> (Information Commissioner's Office) - United Kingdom :
            <a href="https://www.ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >www.ico.org.uk</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>DPA</strong> or equivalent in your Member State of residence
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>13. Changes to this policy</h2>

        <p>
          This policy may be amended at any time to reflect regulatory, technical or organizational
          changes. You will be informed of any material amendments. The applicable version is that
          in force at the time of your consultation.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Contact and questions</h2>

        <p>
          For any questions concerning this policy, the exercise of your rights or the protection of
          your personal data, please contact us at: <br />
          <a href="mailto:contact@all-leaders.fr">contact@all-leaders.fr</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>

<style>
  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul li {
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
